sonusCommonMIB.description: The MIB Module for common management of all Sonus devices.

sonusNetMgmtClientNextIndex.name: sonusNetMgmtClientNextIndex
sonusNetMgmtClientNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating an entry in the sonusNetMgmtClientTable.

sonusNetMgmtClientTable.name: sonusNetMgmtClientTable
sonusNetMgmtClientTable.description: The sonusNetMgmtClientTable specifies the management entities (i.e. clients) that are capable of configurating the node. Each management client is identified by its IP address.

sonusNetMgmtClientIndex.name: sonusNetMgmtClientIndex
sonusNetMgmtClientIndex.description: The tabular index of this administrative management client.

sonusNetMgmtClientName.name: sonusNetMgmtClientName
sonusNetMgmtClientName.description: The name of this administrative management client.

sonusNetMgmtClientState.name: sonusNetMgmtClientState
sonusNetMgmtClientState.description: The administrative state of this management client.

sonusNetMgmtClientIpAddr.name: sonusNetMgmtClientIpAddr
sonusNetMgmtClientIpAddr.description: The IP address of this management client.

sonusNetMgmtClientAccess.name: sonusNetMgmtClientAccess
sonusNetMgmtClientAccess.description: The level of management that is granted to this management client.

sonusNetMgmtClientTrapState.name: sonusNetMgmtClientTrapState
sonusNetMgmtClientTrapState.description: Determines whether SNMP traps are transmitted to this management client.

sonusNetMgmtClientRowStatus.name: sonusNetMgmtClientRowStatus
sonusNetMgmtClientRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete rows in the sonusNetMgmtClientTable.

sonusNetMgmtClientTrapPort.name: sonusNetMgmtClientTrapPort
sonusNetMgmtClientTrapPort.description: The port number of the management client where trap/notification PDUs are to be sent to.

sonusNetMgmtClientAllTraps.name: sonusNetMgmtClientAllTraps
sonusNetMgmtClientAllTraps.description: Indicates if all traps are to be sent to this management client, and defines their trap type.

sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqTimeout.name: sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqTimeout
sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqTimeout.description: The time in seconds that an InformRequest PDU that is sent to this Management Client will timeout if no Response PDU is received. This MIB object does not apply to SNMPv1 or SNMPv2 Trap PDUs. Refer to sonusNetMgmtClientInformRequestRetries for related information.

sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqRetries.name: sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqRetries
sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqRetries.description: The number of retries that are to be made when sending an InformRequest PDU to this Management Client. The maximum number of attempts to send an InformRequest PDU to a Management Client will be one, for the initial attempt, plus the number of retries. This MIB object does not apply to SNMPv1 or SNMPv2 Trap PDUs. Refer to sonusNetMgmtClientInformRequestTimeout for related information.

sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqMaxQueue.name: sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqMaxQueue
sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqMaxQueue.description: The maximum of InformRequest PDUs that will be outstanding, awaiting for Response PDUs from this Management Client. When the maximum number has been reached, consectutive InformRequest PDUs will be discarded (i.e. not sent.) Increasing this number will increase the memory consumed by the GSX software and the CPU time required to process the InformRequest PDUs. This MIB object does not apply to SNMPv1 or SNMPv2 Trap PDUs.

sonusNetMgmtClientStatusTable.name: sonusNetMgmtClientStatusTable
sonusNetMgmtClientStatusTable.description: The sonusNetMgmtClientStatusTable specifies the status of the management entities (i.e. clients). Each management client is identified by its IP address.

sonusNetMgmtClientStatusIndex.name: sonusNetMgmtClientStatusIndex
sonusNetMgmtClientStatusIndex.description: The tabular index of this status management client.

sonusNetMgmtClientStatusLastConfigChange.name: sonusNetMgmtClientStatusLastConfigChange
sonusNetMgmtClientStatusLastConfigChange.description: Octet string that identifies the GMT timestamp of last successful SET PDU from this management client. field octects contents range ----- ------- -------- ----- 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..59 7 8 deci-sec 0..9 * Notes: - the value of year is in network-byte order

sonusNetMgmtTrapTable.name: sonusNetMgmtTrapTable
sonusNetMgmtTrapTable.description: The sonusNetMgmtTrapTable identifies the SNMP Traps that this node supports.

sonusNetMgmtTrapIndex.name: sonusNetMgmtTrapIndex
sonusNetMgmtTrapIndex.description: The tabular index of this trap.

sonusNetMgmtTrapMIBName.name: sonusNetMgmtTrapMIBName
sonusNetMgmtTrapMIBName.description: The full MIB name of this trap.

sonusNetMgmtTrapOID.name: sonusNetMgmtTrapOID
sonusNetMgmtTrapOID.description: The MIB OID of this trap.

sonusNetMgmtTrapClass.name: sonusNetMgmtTrapClass
sonusNetMgmtTrapClass.description: The classification of the event that corresponds to this trap.

sonusNetMgmtTrapLevel.name: sonusNetMgmtTrapLevel
sonusNetMgmtTrapLevel.description: The severity level of the event that corresponds to this trap.

sonusNetMgmtTrapState.name: sonusNetMgmtTrapState
sonusNetMgmtTrapState.description: Determines if this SNMP trap is transmitted to any management client.

sonusNetMgmtNotifyNextIndex.name: sonusNetMgmtNotifyNextIndex
sonusNetMgmtNotifyNextIndex.description: The next valid index to use when creating an entry in the sonusNetMgmtNotifyTable.

sonusNetMgmtNotifyTable.name: sonusNetMgmtNotifyTable
sonusNetMgmtNotifyTable.description: The sonusNetMgmtNotifyTable identifies which management clients are to be notified by which SNMP Traps.

sonusNetMgmtNotifyIndex.name: sonusNetMgmtNotifyIndex
sonusNetMgmtNotifyIndex.description: The table index of notify entries.

sonusNetMgmtNotifyName.name: sonusNetMgmtNotifyName
sonusNetMgmtNotifyName.description: The name of the notification entry.

sonusNetMgmtNotifyMgmtName.name: sonusNetMgmtNotifyMgmtName
sonusNetMgmtNotifyMgmtName.description: The name of the management client that is to be notified of the trap identified by this entry. The value must match an existing sonusNetMgmtClientName in the sonusNetMgmtClientTable.

sonusNetMgmtNotifyTrapName.name: sonusNetMgmtNotifyTrapName
sonusNetMgmtNotifyTrapName.description: The name of the trap that is to be sent to the management client identified by this entry. The value must match an existing sonusNetMgmtTrapName in the sonusNetMgmtTrapTable.

sonusNetMgmtNotifyTrapType.name: sonusNetMgmtNotifyTrapType
sonusNetMgmtNotifyTrapType.description: Identify whether no PDU, a SNMPv1 Trap PDU, SNMPv2 Trap PDU, or SNMPv2 Inform PDU is to be transmitted to this management client.

sonusNetMgmtNotifyRowStatus.name: sonusNetMgmtNotifyRowStatus
sonusNetMgmtNotifyRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete rows in the sonusNetMgmtNotifyTable.

sonusShelfIndex.name: sonusShelfIndex
sonusShelfIndex.description: The shelf index of the event that generated the trap.

sonusSlotIndex.name: sonusSlotIndex
sonusSlotIndex.description: The slot index of the event that generated the trap.

sonusPortIndex.name: sonusPortIndex
sonusPortIndex.description: The port index of the event that generated the trap.

sonusDs3Index.name: sonusDs3Index
sonusDs3Index.description: The DS3 index of the event that generated the trap.

sonusDs1Index.name: sonusDs1Index
sonusDs1Index.description: The DS1 index of the event that generated the trap.

sonusEventDescription.name: sonusEventDescription
sonusEventDescription.description: A description of the event that generated the trap.

sonusEventClass.name: sonusEventClass
sonusEventClass.description: The category of the event that generated the trap.

sonusEventLevel.name: sonusEventLevel
sonusEventLevel.description: The severity level of the event that generated the trap.

sonusSequenceId.name: sonusSequenceId
sonusSequenceId.description: A consecutive number assigned to each trap in a sequence of traps that are sent to one management client. Each management client has its own set of sequence IDs.

sonusEventTime.name: sonusEventTime
sonusEventTime.description: The date and time of the event that generated the trap.

sonusNetMgmtInformReqDiscards.name: sonusNetMgmtInformReqDiscards
sonusNetMgmtInformReqDiscards.description: The number of InformRequest PDUs that were discarded for a Management Client.

sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqQueueFlushedN.name: sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqQueueFlushedNotification
sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqQueueFlushedN.description: The specified number of InformRequest PDUs destined to the specified Management Client were flushed from the InformRequest PDU queue because no Response PDUs were were received from the Management Client. This situtation could occur if the Management Client cannot quickly process and respond to InformRequest PDUs that it receives, or if communications is lost with the Management Client. If this situation occurs occasionally, it is recommended to increase the InformRequest PDU timeout and/or retry values (see sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqTimeout and sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqRetries.) If this situation occurs repeatedly, it is an indication that communications is lost with the Management Client, either because of network problems, or because the Management Client is no longer operational. It is recommended that this device be configured to send a Trap PDU, not an InformRequest PDU, for this Notification to all Management Clients, thus bypassing a problematic InformRequest PDU queue and allowing the situation to be quickly identified and resolved.

sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqQueueFullNoti.name: sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqQueueFullNotification
sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqQueueFullNoti.description: The specified number of InformRequest PDUs destined to the specified Management Client were discard because its InformRequest PDU queue was full. This situtation could occur if the Management Client cannot quickly process and respond to InformRequest PDUs that it receives, or if communications is lost with the Management Client. If this situation occurs occasionally, it is recommended to increase the InformRequest PDU queue size (see sonusNetMgmtClientInformReqMaxQueue.) If this situation occurs repeatedly, it is an indication that communications is lost with the Management Client, either because of network problems, or because the Management Client is no longer operational. It is recommended that this device be configured to send a Trap PDU, not an InformRequest PDU, for this Notification to all Management Clients, thus bypassing a problematic InformRequest PDU queue and allowing the situation to be quickly identified and resolved.
